//@execute 0=17199; 1=17389; 5=17637; 100=30287; -7=14861
// Incoming stack arguments of a method that also has a large frame. A caller-
// stack slot lives at frame.size() + k*8, so with 40 parameters (8 in
// registers, 32 on the stack) and ~3200 live locals every one of them is read
// from past byte offset 16380 -- and they are read again after an intervening
// call, which also forces saves and restores at those offsets.
